There's a checkov failure

```
Check: CKV_AWS_173: "Check encryption settings for Lambda environmental variable"
	FAILED for resource: aws_lambda_function.athena_table_update
	File: /athena.tf:169-191

		169 | resource "aws_lambda_function" "athena_table_update" {
```


In the documentation https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws/latest/docs/resources/lambda_function :

- kms_key_arn - (Optional) Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the AWS Key Management Service (KMS) key that is used to encrypt environment variables. If this configuration is not provided when environment variables are in use, AWS Lambda uses a default service key. If this configuration is provided when environment variables are not in use, the AWS Lambda API does not save this configuration and Terraform will show a perpetual difference of adding the key. To fix the perpetual difference, remove this configuration.

Maybe that’s what the checkov failure is referring to.

I think adding the configuration as follows might work and get past the checkov error:

```
resource "aws_lambda_function" "athena_table_update" {

  ...
  kms_key_arn                    = aws_kms_key.athena_encryption.arn
  environment {
    variables = {
      mod_account = data.aws_caller_identity.mod-platform.account_id
    }
  }
}
```

Then adding the resource `"aws_kms_key" "athena_encryption"` There is an example in dynamodb.tf where they add such resource `resource "aws_kms_key" "dynamo_encryption"`

